---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Navbar from "../components/Navbar.jsx";
---

<MainLayout>
  <Navbar client:load />

  <main class="min-h-screen px-6 pb-28 pt-36">
    <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <p class="mb-6 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § About / Background
      </p>

      <h1 class="mb-12 max-w-4xl text-4xl font-light leading-tight text-slate-100 md:text-5xl">
        Building practical systems while growing into backend-focused full-stack engineering.
      </h1>

      <div class="grid gap-14 lg:grid-cols-[0.85fr_1.15fr]">
        <aside class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
            Current Focus
          </p>

          <ul class="space-y-4 text-sm font-light leading-relaxed text-[#D8E0DD]">
            <li>Backend-focused full-stack applications</li>
            <li>Authentication and protected routes</li>
            <li>PostgreSQL database persistence</li>
            <li>Accessible and calm user interfaces</li>
            <li>Testing, deployment, and documentation</li>
            <li>Technical Japanese and engineering communication</li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <div class="flex max-w-3xl flex-col gap-10 text-base font-light leading-8 text-[#D8E0DD]">
          <p>
            I am a junior full-stack / backend developer building practical web applications with
            React, TypeScript, FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Docker, and GitHub Actions.
          </p>

          <p>
            My work is focused on turning beginner projects into more realistic engineering systems:
            authentication, persistent databases, API structure, protected routes, deployment workflows,
            readable documentation, and maintainable code.
          </p>

          <p>
            I am especially interested in backend systems, accessibility, automation, and products that
            solve real problems in a calm and usable way. My current portfolio includes full-stack
            dashboards, authentication systems, backend APIs, monitoring tools, and Bloom — an accessible
            routine and focus app designed around low-pressure user experience.
          </p>

          <p>
            I use my projects as an engineering lab: each one is a place to practise debugging, architecture,
            Git workflow, deployment, testing, documentation, and explaining technical decisions clearly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mx-auto mt-40 max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mb-24 border-t border-white/20"></div>

      <p class="mb-12 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-[#A5B5A3]">
        § Direction
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Backend Engineering
          </h2>

          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            FastAPI, PostgreSQL, SQLAlchemy, authentication, API structure, testing, and deployment.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Full&#8209;Stack Systems
          </h2>

          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            React, TypeScript, clean UI structure, protected pages, API integration, and user flows.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="border border-white/15 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-normal text-slate-100">
            Technical Communication
          </h2>

          <p class="text-sm font-light leading-7 text-[#D8E0DD]">
            Clear README files, project recaps, debugging notes, and future technical Japanese writing.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</MainLayout>